{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012QdgmdBxgtkt4tovj3QwR9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile all my findings into a comprehensive report. Let me create a summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n**Source Code Layout:**\n```\nralph-burning-rewrite/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.rs                          # CLI entry point (tokio async runtime)\n│   ├── lib.rs                           # Public module exports\n│   ├── adapters/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   └── fs.rs                        # File system adapter (atomic writes, editor invocation)\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                       # Dispatch router for all commands\n│   │   ├── init.rs                      # Initialize workspace\n│   │   ├── flow.rs                      # List/show flow definitions\n│   │   ├── config.rs                    # Get/set/show/edit workspace config\n│   │   ├── project.rs                   # Project select (stub: create/list/show/delete)\n│   │   ├── run.rs                       # Run management (all subcommands stubbed)\n│   │   ├── requirements.rs              # Requirements drafting (all stubbed)\n│   │   ├── daemon.rs                    # Daemon lifecycle (all stubbed)\n│   │   └── conformance.rs               # Conformance testing (all stubbed)\n│   ├── contexts/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── workspace_governance/\n│   │   │   ├── mod.rs                   # Initialization, active project, workspace loading\n│   │   │   └── config.rs                # EffectiveConfig with defaults/TOML merging\n│   │   ├── workflow_composition/\n│   │   │   ├── mod.rs                   # FlowDefinition, built_in_flows()\n│   │   │   ├── contracts.rs             # StageContract, ValidatedBundle, contract evaluation\n│   │   │   ├── payloads.rs              # PlanningPayload, ExecutionPayload, ValidationPayload\n│   │   │   └── renderers.rs             # Deterministic Markdown rendering\n│   │   ├── project_run_record/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   ├── agent_execution/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   ├── conformance_spec/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   └── requirements_drafting/\n│   │       └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   └── shared/\n│       ├── mod.rs\n│       ├── error.rs                     # AppError, ContractError, AppResult<T>\n│       └── domain.rs                    # StageId, FlowPreset, ProjectId, RunId, StageCursor, WorkspaceConfig\n├── tests/\n│   ├── unit.rs                          # Test module aggregator\n│   ├── cli.rs                           # CLI integration tests (currently empty)\n│   └── unit/\n│       ├── domain_test.rs               # StageCursor, ProjectId validation\n│       ├── workspace_test.rs            # Workspace initialization, config roundtrips\n│       ├── config_test.rs               # EffectiveConfig merging, defaults\n│       ├── flow_preset_test.rs          # (referenced, check file exists)\n│       ├── active_project_test.rs       # Active project lifecycle\n│       ├── stage_contract_test.rs       # Contract evaluation, families, schemas\n│       └── renderer_test.rs             # Deterministic rendering, artifact structure\n├── Cargo.toml                           # Dependencies (chrono, clap, serde, tokio, etc.)\n```\n\n### 2. CARGO.TOML DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Key dependencies:**\n- `chrono` 0.4 - Date/time with `clock` and `serde` features\n- `clap` 4.5 - CLI parsing with `derive` feature\n- `serde` + `serde_json` - Serialization/deserialization\n- `schemars` 0.8 - JSON schema generation from Rust types\n- `toml` 0.8 + `toml_edit` 0.22 - TOML parsing and document editing\n- `thiserror` 2 - Error type derive macro\n- `tokio` 1 - Async runtime with `macros` and `rt-multi-thread` features\n- `tracing` + `tracing-subscriber` - Logging/instrumentation\n- Dev: `jsonschema` 0.18, `tempfile` 3 - Testing support\n\n### 3. MAIN.RS ENTRY POINT\n\n**Pattern:**\n```rust\n#[tokio::main(flavor = \"multi_thread\")]\nasync fn main() -> ExitCode {\n    init_tracing();                      // Initialize fmt subscriber\n    let cli = Cli::parse();              // Clap parsing\n    match cli::run(cli).await {\n        Ok(()) => ExitCode::SUCCESS,\n        Err(error) => {\n            eprintln!(\"{error}\");\n            ExitCode::FAILURE\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n- Forbids unsafe code\n- Uses multi-threaded tokio runtime\n- Minimal tracing setup (compact, no targets, no time)\n- Error displays directly to stderr\n\n### 4. SHARED ERROR TYPES\n\n**AppError (src/shared/error.rs)**\n- `AlreadyInitialized { path }` - Workspace config exists\n- `WorkspaceConflict { path }` - Directory exists without config\n- `InvalidStageCursorField { field }` - Cursor fields must be > 0\n- `InvalidIdentifier { value }` - ProjectId/RunId validation\n- `InvalidFlowPreset { flow_id }` - Unknown flow\n- `UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion { version, supported }` - Version mismatch\n- `UnknownConfigKey { key }` / `InvalidConfigValue { key, value, reason }` - Config validation\n- `NoActiveProject` - No active project set\n- `ProjectNotFound { project_id }` - Project doesn't exist\n- `EditorFailed { editor, details }` - Editor invocation failed\n- `NotYetImplemented { command }` - Placeholder for unimplemented commands\n- Transparent delegations: `Io`, `TomlDeserialize`, `TomlSerialize`, `TomlEdit`\n\n**ContractError (src/shared/error.rs)**\n- `SchemaValidation { stage_id, details }` → `FailureClass::SchemaValidationFailure`\n- `DomainValidation { stage_id, details }` → `FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure`\n- `RenderError { stage_id, details }` → `FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure`\n- `QaReviewOutcome { stage_id, outcome }` → `FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**Failure Classes (domain.rs)**\n- `TransportFailure`, `SchemaValidationFailure`, `DomainValidationFailure`, `Timeout`, `Cancellation`, `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n### 5. SHARED DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**StageId (16 variants)**\n- Planning family: `PromptReview`, `Planning`, `DocsPlan`, `CiPlan`\n- Execution family: `Implementation`, `PlanAndImplement`, `ApplyFixes`, `DocsUpdate`, `CiUpdate`\n- Validation family: `Qa`, `Review`, `CompletionPanel`, `AcceptanceQa`, `FinalReview`, `DocsValidation`, `CiValidation`\n- Methods: `display_name()`, `as_str()`\n\n**FlowPreset (4 variants)**\n- `Standard` - Full flow with 8 stages\n- `QuickDev` - Fast flow with 4 stages\n- `DocsChange` - Docs-focused with 4 stages\n- `CiImprovement` - CI-focused with 4 stages\n- Methods: `as_str()`, `description()`\n\n**StageCursor**\n- `stage: StageId`, `cycle: u32`, `attempt: u32`, `completion_round: u32`\n- All fields must be > 0 (validated in `new()`)\n- Factory: `initial(stage)` → (1, 1, 1)\n- Transitions: `retry()` (increment attempt), `advance_stage(stage)`, `advance_cycle(stage)`, `advance_completion_round(stage)`\n- Used for resumable, retryable execution tracking\n\n**ProjectId & RunId**\n- Transparent newtypes wrapping `String`\n- Reject empty, \".\", \"..\", and anything with `/` or `\\`\n- Methods: `new(value)`, `as_str()`\n\n**WorkspaceConfig**\n- `version: u32`, `created_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n- `settings: WorkspaceSettings` (optional, skipped if empty)\n  - `prompt_review: PromptReviewSettings { enabled: Option<bool> }`\n  - `default_flow: Option<FlowPreset>`\n  - `default_backend: Option<String>`\n  - `default_model: Option<String>`\n  - `extra: Table` (for forward compatibility)\n\n### 6. WORKSPACE GOVERNANCE CONTEXT\n\n**Module: src/contexts/workspace_governance/**\n\n**Constants & Defaults:**\n- `WORKSPACE_DIR = \".ralph-burning\"`\n- `WORKSPACE_CONFIG_FILE = \"workspace.toml\"`\n- `ACTIVE_PROJECT_FILE = \"active-project\"`\n- `PROJECTS_DIR = \"projects\"`\n- `PROJECT_CONFIG_FILE = \"project.toml\"`\n- `REQUIRED_WORKSPACE_DIRECTORIES = [\"projects\", \"requirements\", \"daemon/tasks\", \"daemon/leases\"]`\n- `DEFAULT_PROMPT_REVIEW_ENABLED = true`\n- `DEFAULT_FLOW_PRESET = FlowPreset::Standard`\n\n**Core Functions:**\n- `initialize_workspace(base_dir, created_at)` → `WorkspaceInitialization` with `workspace_root` and `config`\n  - Creates `.ralph-burning/` + required subdirs\n  - Renders and writes `workspace.toml`\n  - Errors on existing config or conflict\n- `load_workspace_config(base_dir)` → `WorkspaceConfig` (parses TOML, checks version)\n- `ensure_supported_workspace_version(config)` → `AppResult<()>`\n- `resolve_active_project(base_dir)` → `ProjectId` (reads active-project pointer, validates project exists)\n- `set_active_project(base_dir, project_id)` → `AppResult<()>` (validates project, writes pointer)\n\n**EffectiveConfig (config.rs)**\n- Loads `WorkspaceConfig`, merges with compile-time defaults\n- `ConfigValueSource::Default` or `ConfigValueSource::WorkspaceToml`\n- `ConfigValue` enum: `Bool(bool)`, `FlowPreset(FlowPreset)`, `String(Option<String>)`\n- Methods:\n  - `load(base_dir)` → Self\n  - `get(key)` → `ConfigEntry { key, value, source }`\n  - `set(base_dir, key, value)` → Updated `ConfigEntry` (uses `toml_edit` for non-destructive updates)\n  - `entries()` → Vec of all config entries\n  - Getters: `prompt_review_enabled()`, `default_flow()`, `default_backend()`, `default_model()`\n- Supported keys: `\"prompt_review.enabled\"`, `\"default_flow\"`, `\"default_backend\"`, `\"default_model\"`\n\n### 7. FILE SYSTEM ADAPTER\n\n**Module: src/adapters/fs.rs**\n\n**FileSystem (all static methods):**\n- `create_workspace(workspace_root, workspace_config_str, required_dirs)` - Creates dirs, writes config\n- `read_to_string(path)` - Simple read\n- `write_atomic(path, contents)` - Atomic write with temp file + rename:\n  - Creates parent dirs\n  - Writes to `.{name}.{pid}.{nanos}.tmp`\n  - Syncs to disk\n  - Renames (atomic on POSIX)\n  - Cleans up temp on rename failure\n- `render_workspace_config(config)` → Pretty-printed TOML string\n- `read_active_project(workspace_root)` → `Option<String>` (returns None on NotFound, trims whitespace)\n- `write_active_project(workspace_root, project_id)` - Atomic write to active-project file\n- `open_editor(path)` - Spawns `$EDITOR` or `$VISUAL` or `vi` with file path:\n  - Splits on whitespace for editor command + args\n  - Returns error with exit code or signal info on failure\n\n### 8. CLI ROUTING & IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Module: src/cli/mod.rs**\n\n**Cli & Commands (clap-derived):**\n```rust\nCli {\n    command: Commands\n}\n\nCommands {\n    Init(init::InitCommand),\n    Flow(flow::FlowCommand),\n    Config(config::ConfigCommand),\n    Project(project::ProjectCommand),\n    Run(run::RunCommand),\n    Requirements(requirements::RequirementsCommand),\n    Daemon(daemon::DaemonCommand),\n    Conformance(conformance::ConformanceCommand),\n}\n```\n\n**Dispatch (pub async fn run(cli) → AppResult<()>):**\nRoutes each command to its handler function.\n\n**CLI Implementations:**\n\n**init.rs**\n- No args\n- Handler: Calls `workspace_governance::initialize_workspace(cwd, Utc::now())`\n- Output: Prints workspace root path\n\n**flow.rs**\n- Subcommands:\n  - `list` - Prints all flow presets with descriptions\n  - `show {flow_id}` - Prints detailed flow info (stages, validation profile, final_review flag)\n- Handler calls: `built_in_flows()`, `flow_definition_by_id(flow_id)`\n\n**config.rs**\n- Subcommands:\n  - `show` - Lists all config entries with TOML-like values and sources\n  - `get {key}` - Prints single config value\n  - `set {key} {value}` - Updates TOML, prints confirmation\n  - `edit` - Opens config file in editor, validates after edit\n- Handler uses: `EffectiveConfig::load()`, `EffectiveConfig::set()`, `FileSystem::open_editor()`\n\n**project.rs**\n- Subcommands:\n  - `select {id}` - IMPLEMENTED: Sets active project (validates exists)\n  - `create`, `list`, `show`, `delete` - Stubbed (NotYetImplemented errors)\n- Implemented select calls: `ProjectId::new()`, `workspace_governance::set_active_project()`\n\n**run.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `start`, `resume`, `status`, `history`, `tail --logs`, `rollback --to --hard`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n**requirements.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `draft --idea`, `quick --idea`, `show {run_id}`, `answer {run_id}`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n**daemon.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `start`, `status`, `abort {task_id}`, `retry {task_id}`, `reconcile`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n**conformance.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `list`, `run --filter`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n### 9. WORKFLOW COMPOSITION CONTEXT\n\n**Module: src/contexts/workflow_composition/**\n\n**Flow Definitions (mod.rs):**\n- `FlowDefinition { preset, description, stages: &[StageId], validation_profile }`\n- `ValidationProfile { name, summary, final_review_enabled }`\n- Four built-in flows:\n  1. **Standard** (8 stages): PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → Qa → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQa → FinalReview\n  2. **QuickDev** (4 stages): PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview\n  3. **DocsChange** (4 stages): DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation → Review\n  4. **CiImprovement** (4 stages): CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation → Review\n- Functions: `built_in_flows()`, `flow_definition(preset)`, `flow_definition_by_id(flow_id)`\n\n**Stage Contracts (contracts.rs):**\n- `ContractFamily`: Planning, Execution, Validation\n- `StageContract { stage_id, family }` - Binds stage to family\n- `contract_for_stage(stage_id)` - Registry lookup\n- `all_contracts()` - Returns all 16 contracts\n- **Contract Evaluation Pipeline:**\n  1. Schema validation (deserialize to typed payload)\n  2. Semantic validation (domain rules on payload)\n  3. Outcome check (non-Approved outcomes fail)\n  4. Rendering (deterministic Markdown)\n- `ValidatedBundle { payload, artifact }` - Success type\n- Methods:\n  - `json_schema()` → `RootSchema` (generated from payload types)\n  - `evaluate(&raw_json)` → `Result<ValidatedBundle, ContractError>`\n\n**Payloads (payloads.rs):**\n\n**PlanningPayload** (used by PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan)\n```rust\n{\n    problem_framing: String,\n    assumptions_or_open_questions: Vec<String>,\n    proposed_work: Vec<ProposedWorkItem>,\n    readiness: ReadinessAssessment\n}\n```\n- `ProposedWorkItem { order: u32, summary, details }`\n- `ReadinessAssessment { ready: bool, risks: Vec<String> }`\n- Domain validation: problem_framing non-empty, proposed_work non-empty, orders > 0\n\n**ExecutionPayload** (used by Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate)\n```rust\n{\n    change_summary: String,\n    steps: Vec<ExecutionStep>,\n    validation_evidence: Vec<String>,\n    outstanding_risks: Vec<String>\n}\n```\n- `ExecutionStep { order: u32, description, status: StepStatus }`\n- `StepStatus: Intended | Completed | Skipped`\n- Domain validation: change_summary non-empty, steps non-empty, orders > 0\n\n**ValidationPayload** (used by Qa, Review, FinalReview, CompletionPanel, DocsValidation, CiValidation, AcceptanceQa)\n```rust\n{\n    outcome: ReviewOutcome,\n    evidence: Vec<String>,\n    findings_or_gaps: Vec<String>,\n    follow_up_or_amendments: Vec<String>\n}\n```\n- `ReviewOutcome: Approved | ConditionallyApproved | RequestChanges | Rejected`\n- `is_passing()` returns true only for `Approved`\n- Domain validation: non-passing outcomes require non-empty follow_up_or_amendments\n- Outcome check: Non-passing outcomes fail with `QaReviewOutcome` error\n\n**Renderers (renderers.rs):**\n- `render_planning(stage_id, payload)` → Markdown (Problem Framing, Assumptions, Proposed Work, Readiness)\n- `render_execution(stage_id, payload)` → Markdown (Change Summary, Steps, Validation Evidence, Outstanding Risks)\n- `render_validation(stage_id, payload)` → Markdown (Outcome, Evidence, Findings and Gaps, Follow-up and Amendments)\n- Uses `stage_id.display_name()` for headers\n- Deterministic (no randomness, byte-identical for same input)\n\n### 10. PROJECT RUN RECORD CONTEXT\n\n**Module: src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs**\n\n**Current State: STUB**\n- Only defines `pub const CONTEXT_NAME: &str = \"project_run_record\";`\n- No actual types or functions yet\n\n**Expected Purpose (from error types and domain):**\n- Likely to track execution state of a run:\n  - Current stage cursor\n  - Run metadata (created_at, started_at, etc.)\n  - Execution outcomes per stage\n  - Retry history\n  - Links to project_id, flow_preset\n\n### 11. OTHER STUB CONTEXTS\n\nAll currently contain only `pub const CONTEXT_NAME: &str = \"...\";`:\n- **agent_execution**: \"agent_execution\"\n- **automation_runtime**: \"automation_runtime\"\n- **conformance_spec**: \"conformance_spec\"\n- **requirements_drafting**: \"requirements_drafting\"\n\n### 12. TEST STRUCTURE\n\n**Test organization (tests/unit.rs):**\n```rust\n#[path = \"unit/domain_test.rs\"] mod domain_test;\n#[path = \"unit/flow_preset_test.rs\"] mod flow_preset_test;\n#[path = \"unit/workspace_test.rs\"] mod workspace_test;\n#[path = \"unit/config_test.rs\"] mod config_test;\n#[path = \"unit/active_project_test.rs\"] mod active_project_test;\n#[path = \"unit/stage_contract_test.rs\"] mod stage_contract_test;\n#[path = \"unit/renderer_test.rs\"] mod renderer_test;\n```\n\n**Key Testing Patterns:**\n\n**domain_test.rs:**\n- StageCursor validation (rejects 0 values)\n- StageCursor transitions (cycle, completion_round, attempt independence)\n- ProjectId validation (rejects path-like, empty, \".\", \"..\")\n\n**workspace_test.rs:**\n- Config serialization round-trips\n- Workspace initialization creates required directories\n- Initialization fails on existing workspace\n- Fixture: `initialize_workspace_fixture(base_dir) → PathBuf`\n\n**config_test.rs:**\n- EffectiveConfig loads compiled defaults\n- Config merges workspace TOML overrides\n- Config round-trips extended settings\n- Fixture: Uses `initialize_workspace_fixture()`\n\n**active_project_test.rs:**\n- resolve_active_project fails on missing pointer\n- set_active_project validates project exists\n- set_active_project writes pointer\n- Trimming of newlines in active-project file\n- Rejects path-like values\n- Fixture: `create_project_fixture(base_dir, project_id)` - Creates project dir + project.toml\n\n**stage_contract_test.rs (55 tests):**\n- Registry completeness (all 16 stages have contracts)\n- Family classification (planning, execution, validation)\n- Schema failure short-circuits semantic validation and rendering\n- Domain failure short-circuits rendering\n- Domain validation of each payload family\n- Outcome check (non-passing review outcomes fail)\n- Successful evaluation of all three families\n- JSON schema generation (exists and has content)\n- Schema validation alignment: generated schema rejects = runtime rejects, and vice versa\n- Conformance scenario IDs (SC-EVAL-001 through SC-EVAL-009)\n\n**renderer_test.rs (25 tests):**\n- Determinism (byte-identical repeated renders)\n- Artifact structure (contains expected sections)\n- Stage display names in headers\n- Empty collections rendering\n- Risk rendering in planning\n- Step status rendering in execution\n- Rejection with follow-up in validation\n- Artifact content matches only payload fields (no extraneous backend text)\n\n### 13. UPSTREAM WORKSPACE GOVERNANCE PATTERNS\n\n**From multibackend-orchestration/src/workspace/mod.rs:**\n- `Workspace { root: PathBuf, config: GlobalConfig }`\n- `discover()` - Walks up from CWD to find workspace root\n- `discover_from(start)` - Walks up from specific directory\n- `load(root)` - Loads config from `ralph.toml`\n- `init(root)` - Creates projects/ and templates/ dirs, writes default config\n- Migration logic for legacy active_project from index.json\n\n**From multibackend-orchestration/src/project/state.rs:**\n- `ProjectState { project_id, project_name, created_at, current_loop, current_phase, status, loops, ... }`\n- `Phase: Planning | Implementing | QA | Reviewing | Committing | Completing | FinalReview`\n- `ProjectStatus: Pending | InProgress | Completed | Failed`\n- `SessionRecord` and `SessionStore` for session reuse across loops\n- Rich loop/completion tracking with backends, artifacts, commits\n\n### 14. KEY PATTERNS & CONVENTIONS\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- All public functions return `AppResult<T> = Result<T, AppError>`\n- Errors are descriptive, designed for end-user display\n- ContractError maps to FailureClass for retry semantics\n\n**Serialization:**\n- TOML for configuration (workspace.toml)\n- JSON for stage payloads (contract evaluate input/output)\n- Serde derive across the board\n\n**Domain Validation:**\n- ProjectId/RunId reject path separators and empty values upfront\n- StageCursor fields validated > 0 on construction\n- Workspace config version checked on load\n- Project existence validated before set_active_project\n\n**Async/Await:**\n- All CLI handlers are `pub async fn handle(...) → AppResult<()>`\n- Using tokio multi-threaded runtime\n- No blocking I/O concerns (file ops, editor spawning)\n\n**Atomic Operations:**\n- File writes use temp-file-rename pattern\n- Config updates preserve TOML structure with toml_edit (non-destructive)\n\n**Determinism:**\n- Stage renderers produce byte-identical output\n- No timestamps, UUIDs, or random generation in artifacts\n- Schema generation from payload types is consistent\n\n**Extensibility:**\n- `extra: Table` fields in config structures for forward compatibility\n- Flatten pattern for optional nested settings\n- Context-based module structure allows new contexts without breaking existing code\n\n---\n\nThis completes a thorough exploration of the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase. The project implements a foundational workspace governance layer with complete stage contract evaluation and rendering, fully stubbed CLI with init/flow/config/project implemented, and a clean, testable architecture ready for implementation of the project_run_record and other execution-facing contexts."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad2e91b7dcf5f7c5d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72620\ntool_uses: 48\nduration_ms: 105344</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84e4772c-0822-4fc6-b1d7-1c1f7c7f3e3a","uuid":"71c93fde-f23b-41b7-a91a-72f7b454f1f3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. The full directory structure under ralph-burning-rewrite/src/\n2. The current state of src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs (it's described as a stub)\n3. The current CLI implementations in src/cli/project.rs and src/cli/run.rs\n4. The shared error types in src/shared/error.rs\n5. The adapter layer in src/adapters/fs.rs\n6. The existing test structure under ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/\n7. The Cargo.toml for dependencies\n8. The main.rs entry point\n9. The workspace governance context (since it's upstream and we depend on it)\n10. Any existing model types, ports, or service patterns used in other contexts\n\nBe very thorough - read all the key files in full so I can understand the patterns and conventions used.","agentId":"ad2e91b7dcf5f7c5d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile all my findings into a comprehensive report. Let me create a summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n**Source Code Layout:**\n```\nralph-burning-rewrite/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.rs                          # CLI entry point (tokio async runtime)\n│   ├── lib.rs                           # Public module exports\n│   ├── adapters/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   └── fs.rs                        # File system adapter (atomic writes, editor invocation)\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                       # Dispatch router for all commands\n│   │   ├── init.rs                      # Initialize workspace\n│   │   ├── flow.rs                      # List/show flow definitions\n│   │   ├── config.rs                    # Get/set/show/edit workspace config\n│   │   ├── project.rs                   # Project select (stub: create/list/show/delete)\n│   │   ├── run.rs                       # Run management (all subcommands stubbed)\n│   │   ├── requirements.rs              # Requirements drafting (all stubbed)\n│   │   ├── daemon.rs                    # Daemon lifecycle (all stubbed)\n│   │   └── conformance.rs               # Conformance testing (all stubbed)\n│   ├── contexts/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── workspace_governance/\n│   │   │   ├── mod.rs                   # Initialization, active project, workspace loading\n│   │   │   └── config.rs                # EffectiveConfig with defaults/TOML merging\n│   │   ├── workflow_composition/\n│   │   │   ├── mod.rs                   # FlowDefinition, built_in_flows()\n│   │   │   ├── contracts.rs             # StageContract, ValidatedBundle, contract evaluation\n│   │   │   ├── payloads.rs              # PlanningPayload, ExecutionPayload, ValidationPayload\n│   │   │   └── renderers.rs             # Deterministic Markdown rendering\n│   │   ├── project_run_record/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   ├── agent_execution/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   ├── conformance_spec/\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   │   └── requirements_drafting/\n│   │       └── mod.rs                   # STUB: CONTEXT_NAME only\n│   └── shared/\n│       ├── mod.rs\n│       ├── error.rs                     # AppError, ContractError, AppResult<T>\n│       └── domain.rs                    # StageId, FlowPreset, ProjectId, RunId, StageCursor, WorkspaceConfig\n├── tests/\n│   ├── unit.rs                          # Test module aggregator\n│   ├── cli.rs                           # CLI integration tests (currently empty)\n│   └── unit/\n│       ├── domain_test.rs               # StageCursor, ProjectId validation\n│       ├── workspace_test.rs            # Workspace initialization, config roundtrips\n│       ├── config_test.rs               # EffectiveConfig merging, defaults\n│       ├── flow_preset_test.rs          # (referenced, check file exists)\n│       ├── active_project_test.rs       # Active project lifecycle\n│       ├── stage_contract_test.rs       # Contract evaluation, families, schemas\n│       └── renderer_test.rs             # Deterministic rendering, artifact structure\n├── Cargo.toml                           # Dependencies (chrono, clap, serde, tokio, etc.)\n```\n\n### 2. CARGO.TOML DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Key dependencies:**\n- `chrono` 0.4 - Date/time with `clock` and `serde` features\n- `clap` 4.5 - CLI parsing with `derive` feature\n- `serde` + `serde_json` - Serialization/deserialization\n- `schemars` 0.8 - JSON schema generation from Rust types\n- `toml` 0.8 + `toml_edit` 0.22 - TOML parsing and document editing\n- `thiserror` 2 - Error type derive macro\n- `tokio` 1 - Async runtime with `macros` and `rt-multi-thread` features\n- `tracing` + `tracing-subscriber` - Logging/instrumentation\n- Dev: `jsonschema` 0.18, `tempfile` 3 - Testing support\n\n### 3. MAIN.RS ENTRY POINT\n\n**Pattern:**\n```rust\n#[tokio::main(flavor = \"multi_thread\")]\nasync fn main() -> ExitCode {\n    init_tracing();                      // Initialize fmt subscriber\n    let cli = Cli::parse();              // Clap parsing\n    match cli::run(cli).await {\n        Ok(()) => ExitCode::SUCCESS,\n        Err(error) => {\n            eprintln!(\"{error}\");\n            ExitCode::FAILURE\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n- Forbids unsafe code\n- Uses multi-threaded tokio runtime\n- Minimal tracing setup (compact, no targets, no time)\n- Error displays directly to stderr\n\n### 4. SHARED ERROR TYPES\n\n**AppError (src/shared/error.rs)**\n- `AlreadyInitialized { path }` - Workspace config exists\n- `WorkspaceConflict { path }` - Directory exists without config\n- `InvalidStageCursorField { field }` - Cursor fields must be > 0\n- `InvalidIdentifier { value }` - ProjectId/RunId validation\n- `InvalidFlowPreset { flow_id }` - Unknown flow\n- `UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion { version, supported }` - Version mismatch\n- `UnknownConfigKey { key }` / `InvalidConfigValue { key, value, reason }` - Config validation\n- `NoActiveProject` - No active project set\n- `ProjectNotFound { project_id }` - Project doesn't exist\n- `EditorFailed { editor, details }` - Editor invocation failed\n- `NotYetImplemented { command }` - Placeholder for unimplemented commands\n- Transparent delegations: `Io`, `TomlDeserialize`, `TomlSerialize`, `TomlEdit`\n\n**ContractError (src/shared/error.rs)**\n- `SchemaValidation { stage_id, details }` → `FailureClass::SchemaValidationFailure`\n- `DomainValidation { stage_id, details }` → `FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure`\n- `RenderError { stage_id, details }` → `FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure`\n- `QaReviewOutcome { stage_id, outcome }` → `FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**Failure Classes (domain.rs)**\n- `TransportFailure`, `SchemaValidationFailure`, `DomainValidationFailure`, `Timeout`, `Cancellation`, `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n### 5. SHARED DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**StageId (16 variants)**\n- Planning family: `PromptReview`, `Planning`, `DocsPlan`, `CiPlan`\n- Execution family: `Implementation`, `PlanAndImplement`, `ApplyFixes`, `DocsUpdate`, `CiUpdate`\n- Validation family: `Qa`, `Review`, `CompletionPanel`, `AcceptanceQa`, `FinalReview`, `DocsValidation`, `CiValidation`\n- Methods: `display_name()`, `as_str()`\n\n**FlowPreset (4 variants)**\n- `Standard` - Full flow with 8 stages\n- `QuickDev` - Fast flow with 4 stages\n- `DocsChange` - Docs-focused with 4 stages\n- `CiImprovement` - CI-focused with 4 stages\n- Methods: `as_str()`, `description()`\n\n**StageCursor**\n- `stage: StageId`, `cycle: u32`, `attempt: u32`, `completion_round: u32`\n- All fields must be > 0 (validated in `new()`)\n- Factory: `initial(stage)` → (1, 1, 1)\n- Transitions: `retry()` (increment attempt), `advance_stage(stage)`, `advance_cycle(stage)`, `advance_completion_round(stage)`\n- Used for resumable, retryable execution tracking\n\n**ProjectId & RunId**\n- Transparent newtypes wrapping `String`\n- Reject empty, \".\", \"..\", and anything with `/` or `\\`\n- Methods: `new(value)`, `as_str()`\n\n**WorkspaceConfig**\n- `version: u32`, `created_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n- `settings: WorkspaceSettings` (optional, skipped if empty)\n  - `prompt_review: PromptReviewSettings { enabled: Option<bool> }`\n  - `default_flow: Option<FlowPreset>`\n  - `default_backend: Option<String>`\n  - `default_model: Option<String>`\n  - `extra: Table` (for forward compatibility)\n\n### 6. WORKSPACE GOVERNANCE CONTEXT\n\n**Module: src/contexts/workspace_governance/**\n\n**Constants & Defaults:**\n- `WORKSPACE_DIR = \".ralph-burning\"`\n- `WORKSPACE_CONFIG_FILE = \"workspace.toml\"`\n- `ACTIVE_PROJECT_FILE = \"active-project\"`\n- `PROJECTS_DIR = \"projects\"`\n- `PROJECT_CONFIG_FILE = \"project.toml\"`\n- `REQUIRED_WORKSPACE_DIRECTORIES = [\"projects\", \"requirements\", \"daemon/tasks\", \"daemon/leases\"]`\n- `DEFAULT_PROMPT_REVIEW_ENABLED = true`\n- `DEFAULT_FLOW_PRESET = FlowPreset::Standard`\n\n**Core Functions:**\n- `initialize_workspace(base_dir, created_at)` → `WorkspaceInitialization` with `workspace_root` and `config`\n  - Creates `.ralph-burning/` + required subdirs\n  - Renders and writes `workspace.toml`\n  - Errors on existing config or conflict\n- `load_workspace_config(base_dir)` → `WorkspaceConfig` (parses TOML, checks version)\n- `ensure_supported_workspace_version(config)` → `AppResult<()>`\n- `resolve_active_project(base_dir)` → `ProjectId` (reads active-project pointer, validates project exists)\n- `set_active_project(base_dir, project_id)` → `AppResult<()>` (validates project, writes pointer)\n\n**EffectiveConfig (config.rs)**\n- Loads `WorkspaceConfig`, merges with compile-time defaults\n- `ConfigValueSource::Default` or `ConfigValueSource::WorkspaceToml`\n- `ConfigValue` enum: `Bool(bool)`, `FlowPreset(FlowPreset)`, `String(Option<String>)`\n- Methods:\n  - `load(base_dir)` → Self\n  - `get(key)` → `ConfigEntry { key, value, source }`\n  - `set(base_dir, key, value)` → Updated `ConfigEntry` (uses `toml_edit` for non-destructive updates)\n  - `entries()` → Vec of all config entries\n  - Getters: `prompt_review_enabled()`, `default_flow()`, `default_backend()`, `default_model()`\n- Supported keys: `\"prompt_review.enabled\"`, `\"default_flow\"`, `\"default_backend\"`, `\"default_model\"`\n\n### 7. FILE SYSTEM ADAPTER\n\n**Module: src/adapters/fs.rs**\n\n**FileSystem (all static methods):**\n- `create_workspace(workspace_root, workspace_config_str, required_dirs)` - Creates dirs, writes config\n- `read_to_string(path)` - Simple read\n- `write_atomic(path, contents)` - Atomic write with temp file + rename:\n  - Creates parent dirs\n  - Writes to `.{name}.{pid}.{nanos}.tmp`\n  - Syncs to disk\n  - Renames (atomic on POSIX)\n  - Cleans up temp on rename failure\n- `render_workspace_config(config)` → Pretty-printed TOML string\n- `read_active_project(workspace_root)` → `Option<String>` (returns None on NotFound, trims whitespace)\n- `write_active_project(workspace_root, project_id)` - Atomic write to active-project file\n- `open_editor(path)` - Spawns `$EDITOR` or `$VISUAL` or `vi` with file path:\n  - Splits on whitespace for editor command + args\n  - Returns error with exit code or signal info on failure\n\n### 8. CLI ROUTING & IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Module: src/cli/mod.rs**\n\n**Cli & Commands (clap-derived):**\n```rust\nCli {\n    command: Commands\n}\n\nCommands {\n    Init(init::InitCommand),\n    Flow(flow::FlowCommand),\n    Config(config::ConfigCommand),\n    Project(project::ProjectCommand),\n    Run(run::RunCommand),\n    Requirements(requirements::RequirementsCommand),\n    Daemon(daemon::DaemonCommand),\n    Conformance(conformance::ConformanceCommand),\n}\n```\n\n**Dispatch (pub async fn run(cli) → AppResult<()>):**\nRoutes each command to its handler function.\n\n**CLI Implementations:**\n\n**init.rs**\n- No args\n- Handler: Calls `workspace_governance::initialize_workspace(cwd, Utc::now())`\n- Output: Prints workspace root path\n\n**flow.rs**\n- Subcommands:\n  - `list` - Prints all flow presets with descriptions\n  - `show {flow_id}` - Prints detailed flow info (stages, validation profile, final_review flag)\n- Handler calls: `built_in_flows()`, `flow_definition_by_id(flow_id)`\n\n**config.rs**\n- Subcommands:\n  - `show` - Lists all config entries with TOML-like values and sources\n  - `get {key}` - Prints single config value\n  - `set {key} {value}` - Updates TOML, prints confirmation\n  - `edit` - Opens config file in editor, validates after edit\n- Handler uses: `EffectiveConfig::load()`, `EffectiveConfig::set()`, `FileSystem::open_editor()`\n\n**project.rs**\n- Subcommands:\n  - `select {id}` - IMPLEMENTED: Sets active project (validates exists)\n  - `create`, `list`, `show`, `delete` - Stubbed (NotYetImplemented errors)\n- Implemented select calls: `ProjectId::new()`, `workspace_governance::set_active_project()`\n\n**run.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `start`, `resume`, `status`, `history`, `tail --logs`, `rollback --to --hard`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n**requirements.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `draft --idea`, `quick --idea`, `show {run_id}`, `answer {run_id}`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n**daemon.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `start`, `status`, `abort {task_id}`, `retry {task_id}`, `reconcile`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n**conformance.rs** - ALL STUBBED\n- Subcommands: `list`, `run --filter`\n- All return `NotYetImplemented` error\n\n### 9. WORKFLOW COMPOSITION CONTEXT\n\n**Module: src/contexts/workflow_composition/**\n\n**Flow Definitions (mod.rs):**\n- `FlowDefinition { preset, description, stages: &[StageId], validation_profile }`\n- `ValidationProfile { name, summary, final_review_enabled }`\n- Four built-in flows:\n  1. **Standard** (8 stages): PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → Qa → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQa → FinalReview\n  2. **QuickDev** (4 stages): PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview\n  3. **DocsChange** (4 stages): DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation → Review\n  4. **CiImprovement** (4 stages): CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation → Review\n- Functions: `built_in_flows()`, `flow_definition(preset)`, `flow_definition_by_id(flow_id)`\n\n**Stage Contracts (contracts.rs):**\n- `ContractFamily`: Planning, Execution, Validation\n- `StageContract { stage_id, family }` - Binds stage to family\n- `contract_for_stage(stage_id)` - Registry lookup\n- `all_contracts()` - Returns all 16 contracts\n- **Contract Evaluation Pipeline:**\n  1. Schema validation (deserialize to typed payload)\n  2. Semantic validation (domain rules on payload)\n  3. Outcome check (non-Approved outcomes fail)\n  4. Rendering (deterministic Markdown)\n- `ValidatedBundle { payload, artifact }` - Success type\n- Methods:\n  - `json_schema()` → `RootSchema` (generated from payload types)\n  - `evaluate(&raw_json)` → `Result<ValidatedBundle, ContractError>`\n\n**Payloads (payloads.rs):**\n\n**PlanningPayload** (used by PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan)\n```rust\n{\n    problem_framing: String,\n    assumptions_or_open_questions: Vec<String>,\n    proposed_work: Vec<ProposedWorkItem>,\n    readiness: ReadinessAssessment\n}\n```\n- `ProposedWorkItem { order: u32, summary, details }`\n- `ReadinessAssessment { ready: bool, risks: Vec<String> }`\n- Domain validation: problem_framing non-empty, proposed_work non-empty, orders > 0\n\n**ExecutionPayload** (used by Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate)\n```rust\n{\n    change_summary: String,\n    steps: Vec<ExecutionStep>,\n    validation_evidence: Vec<String>,\n    outstanding_risks: Vec<String>\n}\n```\n- `ExecutionStep { order: u32, description, status: StepStatus }`\n- `StepStatus: Intended | Completed | Skipped`\n- Domain validation: change_summary non-empty, steps non-empty, orders > 0\n\n**ValidationPayload** (used by Qa, Review, FinalReview, CompletionPanel, DocsValidation, CiValidation, AcceptanceQa)\n```rust\n{\n    outcome: ReviewOutcome,\n    evidence: Vec<String>,\n    findings_or_gaps: Vec<String>,\n    follow_up_or_amendments: Vec<String>\n}\n```\n- `ReviewOutcome: Approved | ConditionallyApproved | RequestChanges | Rejected`\n- `is_passing()` returns true only for `Approved`\n- Domain validation: non-passing outcomes require non-empty follow_up_or_amendments\n- Outcome check: Non-passing outcomes fail with `QaReviewOutcome` error\n\n**Renderers (renderers.rs):**\n- `render_planning(stage_id, payload)` → Markdown (Problem Framing, Assumptions, Proposed Work, Readiness)\n- `render_execution(stage_id, payload)` → Markdown (Change Summary, Steps, Validation Evidence, Outstanding Risks)\n- `render_validation(stage_id, payload)` → Markdown (Outcome, Evidence, Findings and Gaps, Follow-up and Amendments)\n- Uses `stage_id.display_name()` for headers\n- Deterministic (no randomness, byte-identical for same input)\n\n### 10. PROJECT RUN RECORD CONTEXT\n\n**Module: src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs**\n\n**Current State: STUB**\n- Only defines `pub const CONTEXT_NAME: &str = \"project_run_record\";`\n- No actual types or functions yet\n\n**Expected Purpose (from error types and domain):**\n- Likely to track execution state of a run:\n  - Current stage cursor\n  - Run metadata (created_at, started_at, etc.)\n  - Execution outcomes per stage\n  - Retry history\n  - Links to project_id, flow_preset\n\n### 11. OTHER STUB CONTEXTS\n\nAll currently contain only `pub const CONTEXT_NAME: &str = \"...\";`:\n- **agent_execution**: \"agent_execution\"\n- **automation_runtime**: \"automation_runtime\"\n- **conformance_spec**: \"conformance_spec\"\n- **requirements_drafting**: \"requirements_drafting\"\n\n### 12. TEST STRUCTURE\n\n**Test organization (tests/unit.rs):**\n```rust\n#[path = \"unit/domain_test.rs\"] mod domain_test;\n#[path = \"unit/flow_preset_test.rs\"] mod flow_preset_test;\n#[path = \"unit/workspace_test.rs\"] mod workspace_test;\n#[path = \"unit/config_test.rs\"] mod config_test;\n#[path = \"unit/active_project_test.rs\"] mod active_project_test;\n#[path = \"unit/stage_contract_test.rs\"] mod stage_contract_test;\n#[path = \"unit/renderer_test.rs\"] mod renderer_test;\n```\n\n**Key Testing Patterns:**\n\n**domain_test.rs:**\n- StageCursor validation (rejects 0 values)\n- StageCursor transitions (cycle, completion_round, attempt independence)\n- ProjectId validation (rejects path-like, empty, \".\", \"..\")\n\n**workspace_test.rs:**\n- Config serialization round-trips\n- Workspace initialization creates required directories\n- Initialization fails on existing workspace\n- Fixture: `initialize_workspace_fixture(base_dir) → PathBuf`\n\n**config_test.rs:**\n- EffectiveConfig loads compiled defaults\n- Config merges workspace TOML overrides\n- Config round-trips extended settings\n- Fixture: Uses `initialize_workspace_fixture()`\n\n**active_project_test.rs:**\n- resolve_active_project fails on missing pointer\n- set_active_project validates project exists\n- set_active_project writes pointer\n- Trimming of newlines in active-project file\n- Rejects path-like values\n- Fixture: `create_project_fixture(base_dir, project_id)` - Creates project dir + project.toml\n\n**stage_contract_test.rs (55 tests):**\n- Registry completeness (all 16 stages have contracts)\n- Family classification (planning, execution, validation)\n- Schema failure short-circuits semantic validation and rendering\n- Domain failure short-circuits rendering\n- Domain validation of each payload family\n- Outcome check (non-passing review outcomes fail)\n- Successful evaluation of all three families\n- JSON schema generation (exists and has content)\n- Schema validation alignment: generated schema rejects = runtime rejects, and vice versa\n- Conformance scenario IDs (SC-EVAL-001 through SC-EVAL-009)\n\n**renderer_test.rs (25 tests):**\n- Determinism (byte-identical repeated renders)\n- Artifact structure (contains expected sections)\n- Stage display names in headers\n- Empty collections rendering\n- Risk rendering in planning\n- Step status rendering in execution\n- Rejection with follow-up in validation\n- Artifact content matches only payload fields (no extraneous backend text)\n\n### 13. UPSTREAM WORKSPACE GOVERNANCE PATTERNS\n\n**From multibackend-orchestration/src/workspace/mod.rs:**\n- `Workspace { root: PathBuf, config: GlobalConfig }`\n- `discover()` - Walks up from CWD to find workspace root\n- `discover_from(start)` - Walks up from specific directory\n- `load(root)` - Loads config from `ralph.toml`\n- `init(root)` - Creates projects/ and templates/ dirs, writes default config\n- Migration logic for legacy active_project from index.json\n\n**From multibackend-orchestration/src/project/state.rs:**\n- `ProjectState { project_id, project_name, created_at, current_loop, current_phase, status, loops, ... }`\n- `Phase: Planning | Implementing | QA | Reviewing | Committing | Completing | FinalReview`\n- `ProjectStatus: Pending | InProgress | Completed | Failed`\n- `SessionRecord` and `SessionStore` for session reuse across loops\n- Rich loop/completion tracking with backends, artifacts, commits\n\n### 14. KEY PATTERNS & CONVENTIONS\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- All public functions return `AppResult<T> = Result<T, AppError>`\n- Errors are descriptive, designed for end-user display\n- ContractError maps to FailureClass for retry semantics\n\n**Serialization:**\n- TOML for configuration (workspace.toml)\n- JSON for stage payloads (contract evaluate input/output)\n- Serde derive across the board\n\n**Domain Validation:**\n- ProjectId/RunId reject path separators and empty values upfront\n- StageCursor fields validated > 0 on construction\n- Workspace config version checked on load\n- Project existence validated before set_active_project\n\n**Async/Await:**\n- All CLI handlers are `pub async fn handle(...) → AppResult<()>`\n- Using tokio multi-threaded runtime\n- No blocking I/O concerns (file ops, editor spawning)\n\n**Atomic Operations:**\n- File writes use temp-file-rename pattern\n- Config updates preserve TOML structure with toml_edit (non-destructive)\n\n**Determinism:**\n- Stage renderers produce byte-identical output\n- No timestamps, UUIDs, or random generation in artifacts\n- Schema generation from payload types is consistent\n\n**Extensibility:**\n- `extra: Table` fields in config structures for forward compatibility\n- Flatten pattern for optional nested settings\n- Context-based module structure allows new contexts without breaking existing code\n\n---\n\nThis completes a thorough exploration of the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase. The project implements a foundational workspace governance layer with complete stage contract evaluation and rendering, fully stubbed CLI with init/flow/config/project implemented, and a clean, testable architecture ready for implementation of the project_run_record and other execution-facing contexts."}],"totalDurationMs":105344,"totalTokens":72620,"totalToolUseCount":48,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2133,"cache_read_input_tokens":63857,"output_tokens":6627,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2133},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
