{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0187kK5weadRHBqQiXp3wnnc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- **Port/adapter architecture**: Introduced `ProjectStorePort`, `JournalStorePort`, `ArtifactStorePort`, `RuntimeLogStorePort`, `RunSnapshotPort`, and `ActiveProjectPort` as trait boundaries in `contexts/project_run_record/service.rs`, with `Fs*` filesystem-backed implementations in `adapters/fs.rs`. This enables fake-port testing without filesystem I/O.\n- **Atomic project creation**: Uses a staging directory (`.{id}.staging.{pid}`) alongside the final project path, writes all canonical files there, then performs a single `rename()` to the final location. On any failure, the staging dir is cleaned up, ensuring no partial projects are visible to `project list` or `project show`.\n- **Journal as NDJSON**: `journal.ndjson` uses one JSON object per line with monotonically increasing `sequence` numbers. Parsing validates sequence ordering and fails fast on gaps or corruption.\n- **Prompt hash**: Used `std::hash::DefaultHasher` (SipHash) for a lightweight, deterministic prompt content hash. This is sufficient for integrity tracking; a cryptographic hash can be substituted later if needed.\n- **Run snapshot separation**: `run.json` stores canonical run state independently. Status, history, and tail commands read from canonical files, never inferring from artifacts or Markdown. The `RunHistoryView` type has no runtime log field, enforcing separation at the type level.\n- **Flow immutability**: `ProjectRecord.flow` is a plain field with no mutation methods. The `create_project` service writes it once; no CLI path or store method allows changing it afterward.\n- **Active-project pointer semantics**: `project create` does not set the active-project pointer (preserving the existing `project select` responsibility). `project delete` clears the pointer only after successful deletion.\n- **Error variants**: Added `DuplicateProject`, `CorruptRecord`, `InvalidPrompt`, `ActiveRunDelete`, `JournalSequence`, and `SerdeJson` to `AppError` for precise error reporting.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- **Payload/artifact write atomicity**: The spec requires that if a payload write succeeds but its artifact companion fails, `run history` and `run tail` must not expose a partial record. This is enforced at query time via `validate_history_consistency()` which rejects orphaned artifacts. The actual atomic write of payload+artifact pairs will be implemented in the `run start` slice (loop 6) since this loop only adds the store models and enumeration APIs.\n- **`run start`, `run resume`, `run rollback`**: These remain as `NotYetImplemented` stubs per the spec's \"keep as later-slice work\" directive.\n- **Adapter contract tests for filesystem round trips**: The filesystem round-trip behavior is covered by the CLI integration tests (which create real projects via the binary and verify file contents). Dedicated adapter-only contract tests were not added separately since the CLI tests provide equivalent coverage with less indirection.\n\n## Testing\n- **103 unit tests** covering domain models, journal sequencing/corruption, query builders, history consistency validation, and service-level tests with fake ports for all CRUD + run query operations.\n- **31 CLI integration tests** covering project create (canonical files, journal init, run.json state, duplicate ID, invalid flow, missing prompt, no-active-set), list (empty, with active marker), show (explicit ID, active resolution), delete (success, active-pointer clear, missing project), and run status/history/tail (not-started, journal events, durable-only default, --logs separation).\n- **2 Gherkin feature files** with 23 scenarios: `project_records.feature` (13 scenarios for CRUD + immutable flow) and `run_queries.feature` (10 scenarios for status/history/tail/corruption).\n- `cargo test` passes all 134 tests. `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` passes clean."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":113,"cache_read_input_tokens":122572,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":113},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84e4772c-0822-4fc6-b1d7-1c1f7c7f3e3a","uuid":"3f31c764-4b43-4691-8f42-c0bf2cf912a2"}
