{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017r2pi3xTD6qbkY4thKztbt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of all the files and structures I've found:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\nI have thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite directory and mapped out the complete codebase structure. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **src/contexts/project_run_record/** - Complete Project Run Record Context\n\n**model.rs** (174 lines):\n- `ProjectRecord` - Immutable metadata persisted in `project.toml` (id, name, flow, prompt_reference, prompt_hash, created_at, status_summary)\n- `ProjectStatusSummary` enum - Created, Active, Completed, Failed\n- `RunSnapshot` - Canonical run state persisted in `run.json` (active_run, status, status_summary)\n- `ActiveRun` - Current run info (run_id, stage_cursor, started_at)\n- `RunStatus` enum - NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `JournalEvent` - Single NDJSON line entry (sequence, timestamp, event_type, details)\n- `JournalEventType` enum - ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n- `PayloadRecord` - History payload stored in `history/payloads/` (payload_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, created_at, payload)\n- `ArtifactRecord` - History artifact in `history/artifacts/` (artifact_id, payload_id, stage_id, created_at, content)\n- `RuntimeLogEntry` - Log entry in `runtime/logs/` (timestamp, level, source, message)\n- `LogLevel` enum - Debug, Info, Warn, Error\n- `RollbackPoint` - Metadata in `rollback/` (rollback_id, created_at, stage_id, cycle, run_snapshot)\n- `SessionStore` - Empty store for `sessions.json`\n- `ProjectListEntry` - Summary for project list output\n- `ProjectDetail` - Detailed view for project show output\n\n**queries.rs** (121 lines):\n- `RunStatusView` - Read model for `run status` (canonical state only)\n- `RunHistoryView` - Read model for `run history` (durable history only: journal + payloads + artifacts, NO runtime logs)\n- `RunTailView` - Read model for `run tail` (durable history by default, with optional runtime logs)\n- `build_status_view()` - Build status view from canonical run state\n- `build_history_view()` - Build history view from durable records only\n- `build_tail_view()` - Build tail view with optional logs\n- `validate_history_consistency()` - Validates every artifact has matching payload\n\n**service.rs** (297 lines):\nPort definitions:\n- `ProjectStorePort` - Reading/writing project records (project_exists, read_project_record, list_project_ids, delete_project, create_project_atomic)\n- `JournalStorePort` - Reading/appending journal events (read_journal, append_event)\n- `ArtifactStorePort` - Reading payload and artifact history (list_payloads, list_artifacts)\n- `RuntimeLogStorePort` - Reading runtime logs (read_runtime_logs)\n- `RunSnapshotPort` - Reading run snapshot (read_run_snapshot)\n- `ActiveProjectPort` - Reading/clearing active project pointer (read_active_project_id, clear_active_project)\n\nService functions:\n- `CreateProjectInput` - Input for project creation\n- `create_project()` - Create new project with all canonical files\n- `list_projects()` - List all projects with summary data\n- `show_project()` - Show detailed project information\n- `delete_project()` - Delete project (fails if active run exists, clears active-project pointer)\n- `run_status()` - Get run status for active project\n- `run_history()` - Get run history (durable only)\n- `run_tail()` - Get run tail with optional runtime logs\n\n**journal.rs** (63 lines):\n- `validate_sequence()` - Validates new event's sequence follows last known (first must be 1)\n- `serialize_event()` - Serializes to single NDJSON line\n- `deserialize_event()` - Deserializes single NDJSON line\n- `parse_journal()` - Parses full journal.ndjson with monotonic sequence validation\n- `last_sequence()` - Returns last sequence or 0 if empty\n\n**mod.rs** - Exports context name, ports, and service use cases\n\n### 2. **src/adapters/fs.rs** - Filesystem Implementation (511 lines)\n\n**FileSystem** utility struct:\n- `create_workspace()` - Create workspace with directories\n- `read_to_string()` - Read file to string\n- `write_atomic()` - Atomic write with temp file + rename pattern\n- `render_workspace_config()` - Render config to TOML\n- `read_active_project()` - Read active project file\n- `write_active_project()` - Write active project file\n- `open_editor()` - Open EDITOR/VISUAL with fallback to vi\n- `prompt_hash()` - Compute simple hash of prompt content\n- Helper path methods for workspace and project layout\n\n**FsProjectStore** - Implements `ProjectStorePort`:\n- `project_exists()` - Check if project dir + project.toml exist\n- `read_project_record()` - Read and parse project.toml\n- `list_project_ids()` - List all valid project IDs\n- `delete_project()` - Delete project directory\n- `create_project_atomic()` - Stage creation in temp dir, atomic rename to final location\n\n**FsJournalStore** - Implements `JournalStorePort`:\n- `read_journal()` - Parse journal.ndjson or return empty on NotFound\n- `append_event()` - Append event line with newline\n\n**FsArtifactStore** - Implements `ArtifactStorePort`:\n- `list_payloads()` - List all .json files in history/payloads/\n- `list_artifacts()` - List all .json files in history/artifacts/\n- Both sorted by created_at\n\n**FsRuntimeLogStore** - Implements `RuntimeLogStorePort`:\n- `read_runtime_logs()` - Read all .ndjson files from runtime/logs/\n\n**FsRunSnapshotStore** - Implements `RunSnapshotPort`:\n- `read_run_snapshot()` - Read run.json or return initial() on NotFound\n\n**FsActiveProjectStore** - Implements `ActiveProjectPort`:\n- `read_active_project_id()` - Read active-project file\n- `clear_active_project()` - Delete active-project file\n\n### 3. **src/cli/project.rs** - Project Command Implementation (215 lines)\n\n**ProjectCommand** with subcommands:\n- `Create(ProjectCreateArgs)` - Create project with id, name, prompt path, flow\n- `Select { id }` - Set active project\n- `List` - List all projects\n- `Show { id }` - Show project details (uses active if no id)\n- `Delete { id }` - Delete project\n\nImplementation:\n- `handle_create()` - Validates workspace, ProjectId, FlowPreset, prompt file, creates with atomic store\n- `handle_list()` - Lists projects with active marker\n- `handle_show()` - Shows project details including journal event count, rollback count\n- `handle_delete()` - Deletes project, shows confirmation\n\n### 4. **src/cli/run.rs** - Run Command Implementation (174 lines)\n\n**RunCommand** with subcommands:\n- `Start` - Start new run (not yet implemented)\n- `Resume` - Resume paused run (not yet implemented)\n- `Status` - Show run status\n- `History` - Show run history\n- `Tail { logs: bool }` - Show run tail with optional logs\n- `Rollback { to, hard }` - Rollback to point (not yet implemented)\n\nImplementation:\n- `handle_status()` - Show project, status, stage, cycle, completion_round, summary\n- `handle_history()` - Show journal events, payloads, artifacts\n- `handle_tail()` - Show durable history and optional runtime logs\n\n### 5. **src/shared/error.rs** - Error Types (107 lines)\n\n**AppError** enum with variants:\n- Workspace: AlreadyInitialized, WorkspaceConflict, UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion\n- Config: UnknownConfigKey, InvalidConfigValue\n- Projects: NoActiveProject, ProjectNotFound, DuplicateProject, ActiveRunDelete\n- Validation: InvalidStageCursorField, InvalidIdentifier, InvalidFlowPreset\n- Prompts: InvalidPrompt\n- Records: CorruptRecord, JournalSequence\n- CLI: EditorFailed, NotYetImplemented\n- Errors from dependencies: Io, TomlDeserialize, TomlSerialize, TomlEdit, SerdeJson\n\n**ContractError** enum:\n- SchemaValidation - Maps to FailureClass::SchemaValidationFailure\n- DomainValidation - Maps to FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure\n- RenderError - Maps to FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure\n- QaReviewOutcome - Maps to FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n### 6. **src/shared/domain.rs** - Domain Types (368 lines)\n\n**FailureClass** enum - TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n**FlowPreset** enum:\n- Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement\n- with as_str(), description(), FromStr impl\n\n**StageId** enum (16 variants):\n- PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n- PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation\n- with display_name(), as_str()\n\n**StageCursor**:\n- stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round\n- Methods: new(), initial(), retry(), advance_stage(), advance_cycle(), advance_completion_round()\n\n**ProjectId** - Validated single-path identifier (no /, \\, empty, ., ..)\n\n**RunId** - Validated non-empty identifier\n\n**WorkspaceConfig** - version, created_at, settings\n\n**WorkspaceSettings** - prompt_review, default_flow, default_backend, default_model, extra\n\n**PromptReviewSettings** - enabled, extra\n\n### 7. **src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs** - Workspace Management (116 lines)\n\n- `WorkspaceInitialization` - workspace_root, config\n- `initialize_workspace()` - Create workspace with validation\n- `load_workspace_config()` - Load and parse workspace.toml\n- `ensure_supported_workspace_version()` - Version check\n- `resolve_active_project()` - Get active project ID with validation\n- `set_active_project()` - Set active project with validation\n- Helper functions for paths and validation\n\n### 8. **src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs** - Config Management (314 lines)\n\n**ConfigValue** enum - Bool, FlowPreset, String(Option)\n\n**ConfigValueSource** enum - Default, WorkspaceToml\n\n**ConfigEntry** - key, value, source\n\n**EffectiveConfig**:\n- load(), get(), set(), entries()\n- prompt_review_enabled(), default_flow(), default_backend(), default_model()\n- From workspace config with defaults\n\n**ConfigKey** enum:\n- PromptReviewEnabled, DefaultFlow, DefaultBackend, DefaultModel\n- with parse(), apply_to_document()\n\nHelper functions for parsing bool, flow preset, optional string\n\n### 9. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs** - Flow Definitions (116 lines)\n\n**ValidationProfile** - name, summary, final_review_enabled\n\n**FlowDefinition** - preset, description, stages, validation_profile\n\n**Four built-in flows**:\n1. **Standard** (8 stages): PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n2. **QuickDev** (4 stages): PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview\n3. **DocsChange** (4 stages): DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, Review\n4. **CiImprovement** (4 stages): CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation, Review\n\nHelper functions: built_in_flows(), flow_definition(), flow_definition_by_id()\n\n### 10. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs** - Stage Contract Registry (239 lines)\n\n**ContractFamily** enum:\n- Planning: prompt_review, planning, docs_plan, ci_plan\n- Execution: implementation, plan_and_implement, apply_fixes, docs_update, ci_update\n- Validation: qa, docs_validation, ci_validation, acceptance_qa, review, final_review, completion_panel\n\n**StageContract**:\n- stage_id, family\n- Methods: json_schema(), evaluate(), validate_schema(), validate_semantics(), render(), check_outcome()\n\n**ValidatedBundle** - payload, artifact\n\nRegistry functions: contract_for_stage(), all_contracts()\n\n### 11. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs** - Payload Models (131 lines)\n\n**PlanningPayload**:\n- problem_framing, assumptions_or_open_questions, proposed_work, readiness\n\n**ProposedWorkItem** - order, summary, details\n\n**ReadinessAssessment** - ready, risks\n\n**ExecutionPayload**:\n- change_summary, steps, validation_evidence, outstanding_risks\n\n**ExecutionStep** - order, description, status\n\n**StepStatus** enum - Intended, Completed, Skipped\n\n**ValidationPayload**:\n- outcome, evidence, findings_or_gaps, follow_up_or_amendments\n\n**ReviewOutcome** enum - Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected\n- is_passing() returns true only for Approved\n\n**StagePayload** enum (tagged union) - Planning, Execution, Validation\n\n### 12. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs** - Markdown Renderers\n\nDeterministic Markdown renderers for validated payloads:\n- `render_planning()` - Renders Problem Framing, Assumptions, Proposed Work, Readiness\n- `render_execution()` - Renders Change Summary, Steps, Validation Evidence, Outstanding Risks\n- `render_validation()` - Renders outcome, evidence, findings, follow-ups\n\n### 13. **src/cli/** - CLI Commands\n\n**init.rs** - Initialize workspace in current directory\n\n**config.rs** - Config management (show, get, set, edit)\n\n**flow.rs** - Flow inspection (list, show with stages)\n\n**project.rs** - Project management (create, select, list, show, delete)\n\n**run.rs** - Run inspection (status, history, tail, start/resume/rollback not implemented)\n\n**conformance.rs** - Conformance tests (list, run - not implemented)\n\n**requirements.rs** - Requirements drafting (draft, quick, show, answer - not implemented)\n\n**daemon.rs** - Daemon management (start, status, abort, retry, reconcile - not implemented)\n\n**mod.rs** - Main CLI dispatcher\n\n### 14. **src/main.rs** - Application Entry Point\n\n- Multi-threaded Tokio runtime\n- Clap CLI parsing\n- Tracing initialization\n- Error handling with exit codes\n\n### 15. **tests/** - Comprehensive Test Suite\n\n**Tests Directory Structure**:\n- `unit.rs` - Test module aggregator\n- `cli.rs` - CLI integration tests\n- `unit/` subdirectory with 10 test files:\n\n**project_run_record_test.rs** (407 lines):\n- Fake port implementations for testing\n- Domain tests: RunSnapshot, SessionStore, ProjectRecord, JournalEvent serialization\n- Service tests with fake ports: create_project, list_projects, show_project, delete_project, run_status\n\n**journal_test.rs** (163 lines):\n- Sequence validation tests (first at 1, monotonic increment, rejects gaps/duplicates/backwards)\n- Serialization/deserialization tests with round-trip\n- Full journal parsing with sequence validation\n- last_sequence() tests\n\n**query_test.rs** (150 lines):\n- RunStatusView tests (not started, running with cursor)\n- RunHistoryView tests (durable records only)\n- RunTailView tests (logs optional, included when requested)\n- History consistency validation tests (matching records, orphaned artifacts)\n\n**stage_contract_test.rs** (comprehensive):\n- Registry completeness tests\n- Contract family mapping tests\n- Contract evaluation tests with valid/invalid payloads\n- Schema validation, semantic validation, rendering tests\n- QA/review outcome failure tests\n- Planning/Execution/Validation payload tests\n\n**renderer_test.rs** - Markdown renderer output tests\n\n**config_test.rs** - Config loading and setting tests\n\n**domain_test.rs** - Domain type validation tests\n\n**flow_preset_test.rs** - Flow preset tests\n\n**active_project_test.rs** - Active project selection tests\n\n**workspace_test.rs** - Workspace initialization tests\n\n### 16. **File System Layout Structure**\n\n**Project structure**:\n```\n.ralph-burning/\n├── workspace.toml\n├── active-project\n├── projects/\n│   └── {project-id}/\n│       ├── project.toml\n│       ├── prompt.md\n│       ├── run.json\n│       ├── journal.ndjson\n│       ├── sessions.json\n│       ├── history/\n│       │   ├── payloads/ (*.json)\n│       │   └── artifacts/ (*.json)\n│       ├── runtime/\n│       │   ├── logs/ (*.ndjson)\n│       │   ├── backend/\n│       │   └── temp/\n│       ├── amendments/\n│       └── rollback/\n```\n\n### 17. **Dependencies** (Cargo.toml)\n\nCore:\n- chrono - Date/time with clock, serde\n- clap - CLI parsing with derive\n- serde/serde_json - Serialization\n- toml/toml_edit - TOML configuration\n- tokio - Async runtime with multi-thread\n- thiserror - Error handling\n- schemars - JSON Schema generation\n- tracing/tracing-subscriber - Logging\n\nDev:\n- jsonschema - Schema validation\n- tempfile - Temporary files for testing\n\n### 18. **CLI Commands Summary**\n\nImplemented:\n- `ralph-burning init` - Initialize workspace\n- `ralph-burning config show/get/set/edit` - Manage workspace config\n- `ralph-burning flow list/show` - View flow definitions\n- `ralph-burning project create/select/list/show/delete` - Manage projects\n- `ralph-burning run status/history/tail` - View run information\n\nNot Yet Implemented:\n- `ralph-burning run start/resume/rollback` - Run execution\n- `ralph-burning requirements draft/quick/show/answer` - Requirements drafting\n- `ralph-burning daemon start/status/abort/retry/reconcile` - Daemon management\n- `ralph-burning conformance list/run` - Conformance testing\n\n---\n\nThis is a well-architected, feature-rich Rust CLI application using clean architecture principles with clear separation between domain logic (contexts), adapters (filesystem), CLI handlers, and comprehensive error handling. The codebase is thoroughly tested with unit tests covering the critical business logic."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0cdb45552278f981 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 82052\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 146778</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3640e08e-b88d-40cb-b39d-a6d9ec8d8fb8","uuid":"5aaf10b4-6218-4ac5-afaf-8887d3f83aca","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the ralph-burning-rewrite directory thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The full structure of src/contexts/project_run_record/ (all files, their contents)\n2. src/adapters/fs.rs - especially project store, journal store, run snapshot store, artifact store implementations\n3. src/cli/project.rs and src/cli/run.rs - current CLI implementations\n4. src/shared/error.rs - current error variants\n5. tests/ directory structure and contents\n6. src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs - current RunSnapshot and other model definitions\n7. src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs - current query implementations\n8. src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs - current service implementations\n9. src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs - journal implementation\n10. The conformance feature files\n\nStart with the directory listing of ralph-burning-rewrite/src/ and ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/, then read all the relevant files. Be very thorough - I need to see all the code.","agentId":"a0cdb45552278f981","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of all the files and structures I've found:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\nI have thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite directory and mapped out the complete codebase structure. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **src/contexts/project_run_record/** - Complete Project Run Record Context\n\n**model.rs** (174 lines):\n- `ProjectRecord` - Immutable metadata persisted in `project.toml` (id, name, flow, prompt_reference, prompt_hash, created_at, status_summary)\n- `ProjectStatusSummary` enum - Created, Active, Completed, Failed\n- `RunSnapshot` - Canonical run state persisted in `run.json` (active_run, status, status_summary)\n- `ActiveRun` - Current run info (run_id, stage_cursor, started_at)\n- `RunStatus` enum - NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `JournalEvent` - Single NDJSON line entry (sequence, timestamp, event_type, details)\n- `JournalEventType` enum - ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n- `PayloadRecord` - History payload stored in `history/payloads/` (payload_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, created_at, payload)\n- `ArtifactRecord` - History artifact in `history/artifacts/` (artifact_id, payload_id, stage_id, created_at, content)\n- `RuntimeLogEntry` - Log entry in `runtime/logs/` (timestamp, level, source, message)\n- `LogLevel` enum - Debug, Info, Warn, Error\n- `RollbackPoint` - Metadata in `rollback/` (rollback_id, created_at, stage_id, cycle, run_snapshot)\n- `SessionStore` - Empty store for `sessions.json`\n- `ProjectListEntry` - Summary for project list output\n- `ProjectDetail` - Detailed view for project show output\n\n**queries.rs** (121 lines):\n- `RunStatusView` - Read model for `run status` (canonical state only)\n- `RunHistoryView` - Read model for `run history` (durable history only: journal + payloads + artifacts, NO runtime logs)\n- `RunTailView` - Read model for `run tail` (durable history by default, with optional runtime logs)\n- `build_status_view()` - Build status view from canonical run state\n- `build_history_view()` - Build history view from durable records only\n- `build_tail_view()` - Build tail view with optional logs\n- `validate_history_consistency()` - Validates every artifact has matching payload\n\n**service.rs** (297 lines):\nPort definitions:\n- `ProjectStorePort` - Reading/writing project records (project_exists, read_project_record, list_project_ids, delete_project, create_project_atomic)\n- `JournalStorePort` - Reading/appending journal events (read_journal, append_event)\n- `ArtifactStorePort` - Reading payload and artifact history (list_payloads, list_artifacts)\n- `RuntimeLogStorePort` - Reading runtime logs (read_runtime_logs)\n- `RunSnapshotPort` - Reading run snapshot (read_run_snapshot)\n- `ActiveProjectPort` - Reading/clearing active project pointer (read_active_project_id, clear_active_project)\n\nService functions:\n- `CreateProjectInput` - Input for project creation\n- `create_project()` - Create new project with all canonical files\n- `list_projects()` - List all projects with summary data\n- `show_project()` - Show detailed project information\n- `delete_project()` - Delete project (fails if active run exists, clears active-project pointer)\n- `run_status()` - Get run status for active project\n- `run_history()` - Get run history (durable only)\n- `run_tail()` - Get run tail with optional runtime logs\n\n**journal.rs** (63 lines):\n- `validate_sequence()` - Validates new event's sequence follows last known (first must be 1)\n- `serialize_event()` - Serializes to single NDJSON line\n- `deserialize_event()` - Deserializes single NDJSON line\n- `parse_journal()` - Parses full journal.ndjson with monotonic sequence validation\n- `last_sequence()` - Returns last sequence or 0 if empty\n\n**mod.rs** - Exports context name, ports, and service use cases\n\n### 2. **src/adapters/fs.rs** - Filesystem Implementation (511 lines)\n\n**FileSystem** utility struct:\n- `create_workspace()` - Create workspace with directories\n- `read_to_string()` - Read file to string\n- `write_atomic()` - Atomic write with temp file + rename pattern\n- `render_workspace_config()` - Render config to TOML\n- `read_active_project()` - Read active project file\n- `write_active_project()` - Write active project file\n- `open_editor()` - Open EDITOR/VISUAL with fallback to vi\n- `prompt_hash()` - Compute simple hash of prompt content\n- Helper path methods for workspace and project layout\n\n**FsProjectStore** - Implements `ProjectStorePort`:\n- `project_exists()` - Check if project dir + project.toml exist\n- `read_project_record()` - Read and parse project.toml\n- `list_project_ids()` - List all valid project IDs\n- `delete_project()` - Delete project directory\n- `create_project_atomic()` - Stage creation in temp dir, atomic rename to final location\n\n**FsJournalStore** - Implements `JournalStorePort`:\n- `read_journal()` - Parse journal.ndjson or return empty on NotFound\n- `append_event()` - Append event line with newline\n\n**FsArtifactStore** - Implements `ArtifactStorePort`:\n- `list_payloads()` - List all .json files in history/payloads/\n- `list_artifacts()` - List all .json files in history/artifacts/\n- Both sorted by created_at\n\n**FsRuntimeLogStore** - Implements `RuntimeLogStorePort`:\n- `read_runtime_logs()` - Read all .ndjson files from runtime/logs/\n\n**FsRunSnapshotStore** - Implements `RunSnapshotPort`:\n- `read_run_snapshot()` - Read run.json or return initial() on NotFound\n\n**FsActiveProjectStore** - Implements `ActiveProjectPort`:\n- `read_active_project_id()` - Read active-project file\n- `clear_active_project()` - Delete active-project file\n\n### 3. **src/cli/project.rs** - Project Command Implementation (215 lines)\n\n**ProjectCommand** with subcommands:\n- `Create(ProjectCreateArgs)` - Create project with id, name, prompt path, flow\n- `Select { id }` - Set active project\n- `List` - List all projects\n- `Show { id }` - Show project details (uses active if no id)\n- `Delete { id }` - Delete project\n\nImplementation:\n- `handle_create()` - Validates workspace, ProjectId, FlowPreset, prompt file, creates with atomic store\n- `handle_list()` - Lists projects with active marker\n- `handle_show()` - Shows project details including journal event count, rollback count\n- `handle_delete()` - Deletes project, shows confirmation\n\n### 4. **src/cli/run.rs** - Run Command Implementation (174 lines)\n\n**RunCommand** with subcommands:\n- `Start` - Start new run (not yet implemented)\n- `Resume` - Resume paused run (not yet implemented)\n- `Status` - Show run status\n- `History` - Show run history\n- `Tail { logs: bool }` - Show run tail with optional logs\n- `Rollback { to, hard }` - Rollback to point (not yet implemented)\n\nImplementation:\n- `handle_status()` - Show project, status, stage, cycle, completion_round, summary\n- `handle_history()` - Show journal events, payloads, artifacts\n- `handle_tail()` - Show durable history and optional runtime logs\n\n### 5. **src/shared/error.rs** - Error Types (107 lines)\n\n**AppError** enum with variants:\n- Workspace: AlreadyInitialized, WorkspaceConflict, UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion\n- Config: UnknownConfigKey, InvalidConfigValue\n- Projects: NoActiveProject, ProjectNotFound, DuplicateProject, ActiveRunDelete\n- Validation: InvalidStageCursorField, InvalidIdentifier, InvalidFlowPreset\n- Prompts: InvalidPrompt\n- Records: CorruptRecord, JournalSequence\n- CLI: EditorFailed, NotYetImplemented\n- Errors from dependencies: Io, TomlDeserialize, TomlSerialize, TomlEdit, SerdeJson\n\n**ContractError** enum:\n- SchemaValidation - Maps to FailureClass::SchemaValidationFailure\n- DomainValidation - Maps to FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure\n- RenderError - Maps to FailureClass::DomainValidationFailure\n- QaReviewOutcome - Maps to FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n### 6. **src/shared/domain.rs** - Domain Types (368 lines)\n\n**FailureClass** enum - TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n**FlowPreset** enum:\n- Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement\n- with as_str(), description(), FromStr impl\n\n**StageId** enum (16 variants):\n- PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n- PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation\n- with display_name(), as_str()\n\n**StageCursor**:\n- stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round\n- Methods: new(), initial(), retry(), advance_stage(), advance_cycle(), advance_completion_round()\n\n**ProjectId** - Validated single-path identifier (no /, \\, empty, ., ..)\n\n**RunId** - Validated non-empty identifier\n\n**WorkspaceConfig** - version, created_at, settings\n\n**WorkspaceSettings** - prompt_review, default_flow, default_backend, default_model, extra\n\n**PromptReviewSettings** - enabled, extra\n\n### 7. **src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs** - Workspace Management (116 lines)\n\n- `WorkspaceInitialization` - workspace_root, config\n- `initialize_workspace()` - Create workspace with validation\n- `load_workspace_config()` - Load and parse workspace.toml\n- `ensure_supported_workspace_version()` - Version check\n- `resolve_active_project()` - Get active project ID with validation\n- `set_active_project()` - Set active project with validation\n- Helper functions for paths and validation\n\n### 8. **src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs** - Config Management (314 lines)\n\n**ConfigValue** enum - Bool, FlowPreset, String(Option)\n\n**ConfigValueSource** enum - Default, WorkspaceToml\n\n**ConfigEntry** - key, value, source\n\n**EffectiveConfig**:\n- load(), get(), set(), entries()\n- prompt_review_enabled(), default_flow(), default_backend(), default_model()\n- From workspace config with defaults\n\n**ConfigKey** enum:\n- PromptReviewEnabled, DefaultFlow, DefaultBackend, DefaultModel\n- with parse(), apply_to_document()\n\nHelper functions for parsing bool, flow preset, optional string\n\n### 9. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs** - Flow Definitions (116 lines)\n\n**ValidationProfile** - name, summary, final_review_enabled\n\n**FlowDefinition** - preset, description, stages, validation_profile\n\n**Four built-in flows**:\n1. **Standard** (8 stages): PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n2. **QuickDev** (4 stages): PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview\n3. **DocsChange** (4 stages): DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, Review\n4. **CiImprovement** (4 stages): CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation, Review\n\nHelper functions: built_in_flows(), flow_definition(), flow_definition_by_id()\n\n### 10. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs** - Stage Contract Registry (239 lines)\n\n**ContractFamily** enum:\n- Planning: prompt_review, planning, docs_plan, ci_plan\n- Execution: implementation, plan_and_implement, apply_fixes, docs_update, ci_update\n- Validation: qa, docs_validation, ci_validation, acceptance_qa, review, final_review, completion_panel\n\n**StageContract**:\n- stage_id, family\n- Methods: json_schema(), evaluate(), validate_schema(), validate_semantics(), render(), check_outcome()\n\n**ValidatedBundle** - payload, artifact\n\nRegistry functions: contract_for_stage(), all_contracts()\n\n### 11. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs** - Payload Models (131 lines)\n\n**PlanningPayload**:\n- problem_framing, assumptions_or_open_questions, proposed_work, readiness\n\n**ProposedWorkItem** - order, summary, details\n\n**ReadinessAssessment** - ready, risks\n\n**ExecutionPayload**:\n- change_summary, steps, validation_evidence, outstanding_risks\n\n**ExecutionStep** - order, description, status\n\n**StepStatus** enum - Intended, Completed, Skipped\n\n**ValidationPayload**:\n- outcome, evidence, findings_or_gaps, follow_up_or_amendments\n\n**ReviewOutcome** enum - Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected\n- is_passing() returns true only for Approved\n\n**StagePayload** enum (tagged union) - Planning, Execution, Validation\n\n### 12. **src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs** - Markdown Renderers\n\nDeterministic Markdown renderers for validated payloads:\n- `render_planning()` - Renders Problem Framing, Assumptions, Proposed Work, Readiness\n- `render_execution()` - Renders Change Summary, Steps, Validation Evidence, Outstanding Risks\n- `render_validation()` - Renders outcome, evidence, findings, follow-ups\n\n### 13. **src/cli/** - CLI Commands\n\n**init.rs** - Initialize workspace in current directory\n\n**config.rs** - Config management (show, get, set, edit)\n\n**flow.rs** - Flow inspection (list, show with stages)\n\n**project.rs** - Project management (create, select, list, show, delete)\n\n**run.rs** - Run inspection (status, history, tail, start/resume/rollback not implemented)\n\n**conformance.rs** - Conformance tests (list, run - not implemented)\n\n**requirements.rs** - Requirements drafting (draft, quick, show, answer - not implemented)\n\n**daemon.rs** - Daemon management (start, status, abort, retry, reconcile - not implemented)\n\n**mod.rs** - Main CLI dispatcher\n\n### 14. **src/main.rs** - Application Entry Point\n\n- Multi-threaded Tokio runtime\n- Clap CLI parsing\n- Tracing initialization\n- Error handling with exit codes\n\n### 15. **tests/** - Comprehensive Test Suite\n\n**Tests Directory Structure**:\n- `unit.rs` - Test module aggregator\n- `cli.rs` - CLI integration tests\n- `unit/` subdirectory with 10 test files:\n\n**project_run_record_test.rs** (407 lines):\n- Fake port implementations for testing\n- Domain tests: RunSnapshot, SessionStore, ProjectRecord, JournalEvent serialization\n- Service tests with fake ports: create_project, list_projects, show_project, delete_project, run_status\n\n**journal_test.rs** (163 lines):\n- Sequence validation tests (first at 1, monotonic increment, rejects gaps/duplicates/backwards)\n- Serialization/deserialization tests with round-trip\n- Full journal parsing with sequence validation\n- last_sequence() tests\n\n**query_test.rs** (150 lines):\n- RunStatusView tests (not started, running with cursor)\n- RunHistoryView tests (durable records only)\n- RunTailView tests (logs optional, included when requested)\n- History consistency validation tests (matching records, orphaned artifacts)\n\n**stage_contract_test.rs** (comprehensive):\n- Registry completeness tests\n- Contract family mapping tests\n- Contract evaluation tests with valid/invalid payloads\n- Schema validation, semantic validation, rendering tests\n- QA/review outcome failure tests\n- Planning/Execution/Validation payload tests\n\n**renderer_test.rs** - Markdown renderer output tests\n\n**config_test.rs** - Config loading and setting tests\n\n**domain_test.rs** - Domain type validation tests\n\n**flow_preset_test.rs** - Flow preset tests\n\n**active_project_test.rs** - Active project selection tests\n\n**workspace_test.rs** - Workspace initialization tests\n\n### 16. **File System Layout Structure**\n\n**Project structure**:\n```\n.ralph-burning/\n├── workspace.toml\n├── active-project\n├── projects/\n│   └── {project-id}/\n│       ├── project.toml\n│       ├── prompt.md\n│       ├── run.json\n│       ├── journal.ndjson\n│       ├── sessions.json\n│       ├── history/\n│       │   ├── payloads/ (*.json)\n│       │   └── artifacts/ (*.json)\n│       ├── runtime/\n│       │   ├── logs/ (*.ndjson)\n│       │   ├── backend/\n│       │   └── temp/\n│       ├── amendments/\n│       └── rollback/\n```\n\n### 17. **Dependencies** (Cargo.toml)\n\nCore:\n- chrono - Date/time with clock, serde\n- clap - CLI parsing with derive\n- serde/serde_json - Serialization\n- toml/toml_edit - TOML configuration\n- tokio - Async runtime with multi-thread\n- thiserror - Error handling\n- schemars - JSON Schema generation\n- tracing/tracing-subscriber - Logging\n\nDev:\n- jsonschema - Schema validation\n- tempfile - Temporary files for testing\n\n### 18. **CLI Commands Summary**\n\nImplemented:\n- `ralph-burning init` - Initialize workspace\n- `ralph-burning config show/get/set/edit` - Manage workspace config\n- `ralph-burning flow list/show` - View flow definitions\n- `ralph-burning project create/select/list/show/delete` - Manage projects\n- `ralph-burning run status/history/tail` - View run information\n\nNot Yet Implemented:\n- `ralph-burning run start/resume/rollback` - Run execution\n- `ralph-burning requirements draft/quick/show/answer` - Requirements drafting\n- `ralph-burning daemon start/status/abort/retry/reconcile` - Daemon management\n- `ralph-burning conformance list/run` - Conformance testing\n\n---\n\nThis is a well-architected, feature-rich Rust CLI application using clean architecture principles with clear separation between domain logic (contexts), adapters (filesystem), CLI handlers, and comprehensive error handling. The codebase is thoroughly tested with unit tests covering the critical business logic."}],"totalDurationMs":146778,"totalTokens