{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XbPfSh1Wo5Dn7hmFT6Lucu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01W2yicF1y7KH1czjviU1kYS","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/tmp/logs/20260311201939-impl-response-001.md","content":"# Implementation Response (Iteration 1)\n\n## Changes Made\n1. **Canonical run snapshot schema** — Expanded `RunSnapshot` in `model.rs` with `cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>`, `completion_rounds: u32`, `rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta`, and `amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState`. Added corresponding `CycleHistoryEntry`, `RollbackPointMeta`, and `AmendmentQueueState` types with `#[derive(Default)]`. Updated `RunSnapshot::initial()` to populate all fields with empty/zero defaults. The serialized `run.json` now contains every canonical field the spec requires.\n\n2. **Durable history completeness** — Updated `validate_history_consistency` in `queries.rs` to check both directions: orphaned artifacts (artifact without payload) AND orphaned payloads (payload without artifact). Updated `handle_tail` in `cli/run.rs` to render payload and artifact records in the durable section, matching what `run history` displays. `run tail` now shows the same durable history as `run history`.\n\n3. **Fail-fast canonical reads** — Changed `FsJournalStore::read_journal` and `FsRunSnapshotStore::read_run_snapshot` in `fs.rs` to return `CorruptRecord` errors when the canonical file is missing (instead of silently returning empty state). Missing `journal.ndjson` now produces `\"canonical file is missing\"` instead of an empty event list. Missing `run.json` now produces the same error instead of a synthesized `RunSnapshot::initial()`.\n\n4. **Delete failure semantics** — Replaced `fs::remove_dir_all` in `FsProjectStore::delete_project` with a two-phase transactional approach: (1) atomic rename to a trash path (`.{id}.deleting.{pid}`), (2) remove the trash directory. If removal fails, the project is renamed back to its original location so it remains addressable. The active-project pointer is only cleared in `service::delete_project` after the store delete succeeds (unchanged).\n\n## Could Not Address\nNone\n\n## Pending Changes (Pre-Commit)\n\n### Files modified:\n- `src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` — New types + expanded RunSnapshot\n- `src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs` — Bidirectional history consistency validation\n- `src/adapters/fs.rs` — Fail-fast reads, transactional delete\n- `src/cli/run.rs` — Payload/artifact display in `run tail`\n- `tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` — Updated RunSnapshot construction in fake store\n- `tests/unit/query_test.rs` — New tests: orphaned payload, schema completeness, round-trip\n- `tests/cli.rs` — New tests: fail-fast missing run.json, missing journal.ndjson, corrupt run.json, run.json schema fields\n- `tests/conformance/features/project_records.feature` — SC-PROJ-014 (transactional delete), SC-PROJ-015 (run.json schema)\n- `tests/conformance/features/run_queries.feature` — SC-RUN-011 through SC-RUN-014 (fail-fast, orphaned payload, tail completeness)\n\n### Test results:\n- `cargo test`: 106 unit + 35 CLI integration = 141 total, all passing\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`: clean\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":114,"cache_read_input_tokens":114642,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":114},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3640e08e-b88d-40cb-b39d-a6d9ec8d8fb8","uuid":"96d1720f-925b-491a-8870-5b41af20de01"}
