{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AQmu7Anh61ne4m1CbwbcCp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RBHFYLGLf4VzkroD99HAcW","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/004-project-and-run-record-foundation/20260311203117-impl-response-002.md","content":"# Implementation Response (Iteration 2)\n\n## Changes Made\n1. **Run snapshot semantic validation** — Added `RunSnapshot::validate_semantics()` that rejects inconsistent status/active_run combinations: `running` or `paused` with `active_run = null`, and `not_started` with `active_run` present. `FsRunSnapshotStore::read_run_snapshot` now calls this validation after JSON deserialization, so all consumers (including `run status`, `project delete`, and `project show`) get fail-fast behavior for corrupt canonical state.\n\n2. **Terminal state reporting in `run status`** — Added `RunStatus::display_str()` returning canonical human-readable strings. `RunStatusView::from_snapshot` now uses this for both active and non-active branches, so terminal states (`completed`, `failed`) without an active run are reported correctly instead of collapsing to \"not started\".\n\n3. **Missing `project.toml` fails fast as corruption** — `FsProjectStore::project_exists` now returns `CorruptRecord` when a project directory exists but `project.toml` is missing (previously returned `false`). `list_project_ids` now returns `CorruptRecord` for non-hidden directories missing `project.toml` (previously silently skipped). `read_project_record` now distinguishes between a missing directory (`ProjectNotFound`) and a directory with missing `project.toml` (`CorruptRecord`).\n\n4. **Test coverage** — Added 7 new CLI integration tests: 3 for missing `project.toml` corruption (show/list/delete), 1 for terminal completed state reporting, 2 for semantically inconsistent snapshot detection (run status and project delete), plus 1 for completed terminal state deletion. Added 7 new unit tests: 3 for semantic validation rejection, 2 for terminal state validation acceptance, 2 for terminal state run status reporting. Added 4 new conformance scenarios in `project_records.feature` (SC-PROJ-016 through SC-PROJ-018) and 4 in `run_queries.feature` (SC-RUN-015 through SC-RUN-018).\n\n## Could Not Address\nNone\n\n## Pending Changes (Pre-Commit)\n- 10 files modified: model.rs, queries.rs, fs.rs, project_run_record_test.rs, query_test.rs, cli.rs, project_records.feature, run_queries.feature\n- 157 tests passing (41 CLI + 116 unit), clippy clean\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":183,"cache_read_input_tokens":104119,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":183},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1a3d9a31-afc3-4ac3-baa7-2cce587b25ae","uuid":"80ddd43e-e20f-48ba-b07f-1a2d1a121175"}
