{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018eoFjC8c8uoR5iVJLa57y7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. The `resolve_active_project` function in `workspace_governance/mod.rs` only checks that `project.toml` exists as a file (line 108: `project_root.join(PROJECT_CONFIG_FILE).is_file()`), but doesn't actually parse it. So if `project.toml` is present but corrupt/malformed, the function returns the project ID successfully, and downstream commands like `run status`, `run history`, `run tail` never read the project record - they just use the project ID directly.\n\nThe fix should ensure that when the active project is resolved, the canonical `project.toml` is actually parsed. This can be done by:\n\n\n1. Modifying `validate_project_exists` to actually parse `project.toml`, or\n2. Adding a validation step in the run command handlers, or\n3. Adding a `validate_project_canonical` function that both checks existence and parses the file\n\nThe cleanest approach is to update `validate_project_exists` to actually parse the TOML file, since it's called by `resolve_active_project`. But wait - `validate_project_exists` is also called by `set_active_project`, and that should probably validate too. Actually, looking more carefully, the real issue is that `resolve_active_project` calls `validate_project_exists` which only checks file existence without parsing, so I need to ensure the TOML is actually validated when the active project is resolved.\n\nNow I'm checking which service functions actually read the project record versus which ones just grab the project ID from `resolve_active_project` without further validation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14759,"cache_read_input_tokens":26080,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14759},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"stand